description:
Now, we uncover the life of Thomas Cranmer, who went from a peaceful life at Cambridge University, to becoming the Archbishop of Canterbury - albeit in a very unconventional way. He was then taken prisoner in the Tower of London because of his Protestant beliefs, and unfortunately died a martyrs death in Oxford. He was of the highest profile of all those who died during Mary Tudors gruesome reign, but perhaps the most courageous at the end.

To find out more about Thomas Cranmer read our extended article on our website.
